All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AddPart
The AddPart controller controls the components used to create and add a part to the inventory.
AddProduct
The AddProduct controller controls the components used to create and add a new product to the inventory.
Alerts
The Alerts class contains the methods used to notify the user of errors and confirm destructive/altering actions
Helpers
The Helpers class contains a variety of methods used in the controller classes.
InHouse
The InHouse class inherits attributes from abstract class Part and adds Machine ID attribute.
Inventory
The Inventory class contains a list of all products and parts in the inventory, methods to retrieve and set the lists; and methods to update, add, lookup, and delete individual parts and products.
Main
The Main class sets the initial scene and launches the application.
MainWindow
The MainWindow controller controls the components of the initial scene and acts as the "home page" for the application.
ModifyPart
The ModifyPart controller controls the components used to edit the values and subclass (InHouse or Outsourced) of the selected part.
ModifyProduct
The ModifyProduct controller controls the components used to edit the values and associated parts of the selected product.
OutSourced
The Outsourced class inherits attributes from abstract class Part and adds a 'Company Name' attribute.
Part
 
Product
The Product class contains the attributes of each product, including a list of all associated parts.
